This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama in August 2013. The executive order is aimed at improving chemical facility safety and security in the United States. It establishes a Chemical Facility Safety and Security Working Group, which consists of various government agencies, to coordinate efforts in improving safety measures. The working group is tasked with developing a plan to support collaboration between state regulators, emergency responders, facility owners and operators, and local communities to enhance safety and security. The executive order also calls for enhanced federal coordination, information collection and sharing, and policy and regulation modernization to ensure the safe handling and storage of chemicals. The working group is also directed to identify best practices and share them with stakeholders in order to reduce safety and security risks associated with chemical production and storage. The executive order emphasizes the importance of implementing these measures within the framework of applicable laws and international trade obligations.